  m_text: "Finally, let's see how to use text assets in game. \nDownload the provided
    \"Dungeon.txt\" file and put it the project directory, under Assets > Story.
    Unity will automatically import it into a TextAsset object, as it does for all
    other supported data types (3D meshes, images, animations, video, audio, etc).\n\nOpen
    the file: it contains 4 chapters of a story, separated by a \"---\" line. As
    an overview, in this room we will implement interaction with in-game objects,
    which will result in displaying these chapters on the game UI."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
