  m_text: 'Lastly, under the Canvas, create a Button object. Double click on the
    Canvas and edit the button manually to adjust its size, and place it on the right
    half of the Canvas. Find the Text object inside the Button and edit the text
    to "Resume". Edit MenuInteraction so that the Button only shows when the game
    is paused.


    EXERCISE 3: Buttons allow to define interaction via their "OnClick()"
    settings. Now, create a public function inside MenuInteraction that unpauses
    the game, then bind the new function to the Button you just created.'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
