  m_text: "Let's start with UI basics: from the Hierarchy, right click > Create >
    UI > Canvas. \n\nCanvas define a bi-dimensional space which we generally use
    for UI elements.\n\nOne very important aspect of canvas is their render space,
    which can either be Screen or World. For example, this text is on a World space
    Canvas object, which means it is rendered in the same \"procedure\" as all other
    3D objects.\n\nScreen space Canvas, instead, are rendered separately as 2D objects
    and overlayed to the 3D render."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
